detailed_reviews.review_text: Love coming to this place for interior decor. When the holidays come around it is the best place to get quality themed kitchen ware and decor. They have so many different options. From clothing to gym equipment to stationary. Find great things the more often you visit.
Always enjoy the occasional shopping trip to Winners. This is a spacious store with plenty of parking. Dog-Friendly, too!

Shout out to the home sense team! We bought a sofa here and from start to finish staff were friendly and very helpful. They help me load the sofa into my truck as well! Cant say enough good things about this location! Great job!
Great offers, nice pricing. Really worth visiting it.
Nisha and Eva very helpful and kind. We bought a Muvado wrist watch and a marble top side table if it helps to remember us! Thanks for the service!

Every thing you need around your house, your patio, is right here...8 acres under covered air conditioning big supercenter. There Are shoes.., jewellery, fashions too... My son found 2 exceptionally comfy, large cushions, for his big van..to rest at the back of van ...on long trips like driving up prince George. Price is good. A spacious stores. Lots of parking and customers, despite in a pretty remote location in Burnaby. I can see lots customers, Lots of choices for happy campers..moving bought products onto their vehicle.

The Winners & Homesence combination store is the only way to go if you plan on spending money. I cant imagine walking out of this combination store without something I needed. If you like something, but you dont like making impulsive shopping decisions, my suggestion is to go and have a coffee or take a little breather outside. Make the decision whether you ARE or NOT going to buy after you remove yourself from all the stimulation of all the stuff set up in such a way that you cant help but desire it ...but just make sure that you dont remove yourself for too long. Because if you go home and think about it and come to decide, after a good nights sleep, that you absolutely MUST have it...guess what its no longer going to be there. It will be GONE. This has happened to me so many times!! This is how I used to make purchases. Any item that I loved when I was in the store and was still thinking about the next day, would be something I believed worth buying. There is such a range of stylish on-trend clothes, accessories, make-up, furniture, decor etc from sandals & giant wall clocks to doggie dresses & mens cologne that you will find what you forgot you needed without much effort at all and at decent prices. Check out my pretty towels and the cutest ever portable doggy bed.
Always great items
Very spacious store with good variety of things. From clothes to beauty item you will surely find something to buy. Employees are helpful and store is well maintained :)
Awesome place to find things for home decor and fashion.

HomeSense really disappoints. The prices arent as good as they used to be, but whoever does the buying is a genius. Although the clothing is pretty nice and winners, I find that they dont always keep up to the newest fashion trends. However the buyer is for the jewelry department really picked some gorgeous pieces. Husbands and boyfriends listen up, this is a great place to get a beautiful piece of jewelry for your loved one at a pretty reasonable price.

I am like a kid on a candy store when visiting Winners & HomeSense. Always grab a cart because even if you don t intend to purchase something I guarantee you, you will not walk out empty handed  . Love the selection they offer, always something new. Staff is always super nice, especially the ladies in the jewellery department. Big plus that they allow dogs and convenient parking is a huge bonus.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Great selection, wasnt busy, and staff said hello shortly after we entered. Have shopped here 1/2 a doz times over the last couple years, and I will go back again.

Marks Work Wearhouse (And why you should shop there!) About a year ago I was diagnosed with Type 2 Diabetes. I had just purchased 4 mens dress shirts, size XXL relaxed fit. I wore one shirt, and the remaining 3 shirts sat in the drawer unopened. I have spent the last 10+ months eating healthy (Keto Lifestyle) and exercising daily. I routinely walk a minimum of 8 kilometers per day, and up to 20 - 30 kilometers on Saturdays and Sundays . . . rain, snow, or shine. I have recently got back on my road bike as well. As a result, my body size has reduced dramatically. I now wear a mens L or XL, slim fit and my waist is now 32.5 (down from 44) I contacted Marks Work Wearhouse in-store to find out if I could exchange the unopened shirts I purchased online. Sadly the store clerk couldnt help me, but she was very nice and apologized. I contacted Marks Work Wearhouse online and within a couple of weeks, smaller sized shirts have arrived on my doorstep. I was told by Marks Work Wearhouse to donate the unopened XXL shirts to charity. The Lady from Marks also congratulated me on my accomplishment. This is a great example of a community oriented company going above and beyond the call. At least for me, they have a satisfied customer for life. This is why I will always shop at Marks Work Wearhouse.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Two of the male employees were really nice and patient in answering my questions and getting what I needed yesterday. Customer service was fantastic

Great experience at this Mark s location. Clean, bright interior and everything is well-stocked. I was looking for women s work gloves and hiking boots, and Brett gave an outstanding customer service. This will be our go-to Mark s from now on!
I bought some sandals online but they were too big. I went down to the store with them and exchanged them quickly for a pair that fit.
They didnt have the boots I was looking for, but the staff was very helpful, friendly, and patient.

Very helpful staff, absolute great customer service: bought a pair of timberland waterproof work boots like 2 and half months prior using  em, turned out to be defective (water leaking in ) after a couple of uses and the guys were able to credit me the whole amount I paid for them; this way I could get a new pair Recommended for all your work wear needs hands down
Very friendly service. And one time I forgot a to save my receipt that I needed for work and Mathew was very helpful getting me a copy.

Awesome customer service! Whoever the manager was she deserves a raise. My boots tore after 8 months of use and she did all she could to rectify the issue. I will happily shop there knowing there are great staff who are willing to help. Thank you (I wish I knew your name) for helping me, I truly appreciate it. Friendly staff and great service. Another happy customer.

This is my absolute favourite Marks location! Matthew was amazing with helping me find the right item - by far one of the best customer service experiences Ive had. The staff work especially hard to keep the place as organized as it is and it shows.

Marks. North Van on Marine. Good selection. They are having a sale for pretty much all items. I bought some items in preparation of Christmas. There were people in the store and the cash register staff were able to move people quickly so the wait time was about 30seconds.  The emailed me the receipt and it was correct. I spent just over $100 and saved $20 from the sale prices.

I had a great experience shopping at this location. Chris was very helpful and went above and beyond for helping me out and finding what I needed. I was looking for a shoe size that was not availible on the sales floor and asked if they had any out back in the storage. After finding out they did not have it at their store, he looked at the other North Vancouver location for me and called them to confirm so he could save me the drive. After finding out that they were out as well (Even though the system showed that they had 1)  Chris placed an order for me where it was shipped to my house 2 days after the purchus date. Great customer service Chris, I appriciate it and will be back at this store again. Thank you Marks Marine Drive and Chris for your outstanding customer service! Al

The young staff member was awesome, Marks prices are great, the quality is top notch!  Their winter sale is 70% off!  Their free socks coupon one Christmas,  many years ago is a fun memory for my family

Excellent store for well built non-frill clothing. Work pants, work jackets and boots. Suited for all inclement weather. The staff are really helpful. The best customer service I have ever had in a marks ever!!! A manager named Marley helped me find the perfect boots! Will shop here forever, even though its a little bit ot of my way.
